events.name: Video Like a Boss: Enterprise Video in the Cloud

group.name: GDG Cloud Twin Cities - A Google Developer Group

events.description:
Agenda:
6:00 PM to 6:30PM food and beverages
6:30 PM to 8:00PM lightning talks, main presentation, and networking

We're going to have up to 2 lightning talks this month, please message the organizers via Meetup if you'd like to present one.

After lightning talks we have Eugene Medynskiy of Kaltura presenting on some really cutting edge video processing in the Google Cloud Platform. Details below.

Venue this month is Improving in Bloomington (where we had the November Meetup).

Main presentation details:

Video Like a Boss: Enterprise Video in the Cloud
70% of internet traffic is video content. Globally, the average person who watches online video does so for seven hours every week, and this amount — including video for work or education — is growing every year. In this presentation, we’ll take a developer’s view at how pre-recorded video is delivered online. We’ll review the steps it takes to get video from “glass-to-glass”: Ingestion, Transcoding, Storage, Enrichment, Packaging, Delivery, and Playback. Understanding these steps will allow any developer to build the cloud-based workflows required to deliver video for common use cases, such as e-commerce (e.g. video product reviews), learning (e.g. training and on-boarding videos), and digital signage. We will finish by looking at the cutting edge of video delivery: Google’s Video AI cloud service, and low-latency live streaming.

Bio
Eugene is the Head of Engineering, Professional Services, at Kaltura. His team works on customized video platform solutions for the world’s largest enterprises and educational institutions.

events.name: Intro to SRE (Site Reliability Engineering)

venue.name: Online Meeting (we'll share the URL before the meeting)

group.name: GDG Cloud Twin Cities - A Google Developer Group

events.description:
Agenda:
6:45 PM to 7:00PM virtual networking, sharing work from home tips and tricks (bring your WFH tips), and event intro
7:00 PM to 8:00PM presentation followed by Q and A

Jose Andrade of Google will present on the topic of Site Reliability Engineering.

Description:
What is Site Reliability Engineering? How does it compare to DevOps? How does Google do SRE? What are SLIs, SLOs and Error Budgets? How to do Risk Analysis and get a Product Maturity Assessment. All these questions can be answered during a brief presentation

Speaker Bio:
Jose Andrade is a Senior Solutions Consultant at Google specializing on infrastructure, SRE/DevOps and large-scale migrations. He has over 18 years of experience working in technology, on topics that range from software development to networking and systems administration. He currently helps large enterprise customers implement cloud technologies with a focus on reliability and scalability and helps startups run their applications efficiently in GCP.

Before joining Google, Jose was a Senior Solutions Architect at Yale University, where he led a team of Senior DevOps Engineers in the development and implementation of custom solutions for consumption and automation of cloud services. He also worked for the federal Judiciary as a software engineer, and was a founding editor and technology journalist with Engadget. He has organized DevOps conferences and community meet-ups with the goal of creating a more inclusive and diverse culture.

Jose holds a Master's degree in Information Management Systems from Harvard University and a BS in Management Information Systems from Liberty University.

In his spare time he enjoys traveling the world with his wife and daughter.

Twitter: @jandrade
